LSU, Alabama Top Season’s 1st Bowl Championship Series Rankings

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-10-17T00:53:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/lsu-alabama-top-season-s-1st-bowl-championship-series-rankings.html
Louisiana State University  and the
University of Alabama hold the top two spots in college
football’s first Bowl Championship Series standings of the
season.  LSU (7-0) has a .9522 BCS rating out of 1.000, while
Southeastern Conference rival Alabama (7-0) is at .9519. They’re
followed by fellow unbeatens Oklahoma, Oklahoma State, Boise
State, Wisconsin, Clemson and Stanford.  The teams finishing No. 1 and No. 2 in the final BCS
standings will play for the national championship on Jan. 9 in
 New Orleans . The BCS is determined using the USA Today coaches’
poll, Harris Interactive poll and six computer rankings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  